---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Regions — Made the Weekend"
  description="UK weekend guides grouped by region. Deep local coverage, added as we get to know each corner."
>
<section class="page-head">
  <div class="inner">
    <svg class="page-motif" width="120" height="44" viewBox="0 0 120 44" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
  <path d="M4 40 C 30 34, 40 22, 60 20 C 74 18.5, 82 17, 89 14" stroke="#E0A45C" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="0.5 7" opacity="0.8"></path>
  <path d="M98 2 C 101.3 2, 104 4.7, 104 8 C 104 12.5, 98 17.5, 98 17.5 C 98 17.5, 92 12.5, 92 8 C 92 4.7, 94.7 2, 98 2 Z" stroke="#E0A45C" stroke-width="1.4" fill="none"></path>
  <circle cx="98" cy="7.8" r="1.8" fill="#E0A45C"></circle>
</svg>
    <p class="eyebrow">Browse by region</p>
    <h1>Where do you fancy?</h1>
    <p class="lede">Five corners of the country so far, each covered as we get to know it. More regions join the map as we drive them.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="light" style="padding-top:clamp(48px,7vw,72px);padding-bottom:clamp(64px,9vw,100px);">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="grid3" style="gap:32px;"><a class="r-card" href="/coming-soon">
  <div class="thumb"><div class="img" data-ph="South West — Dartmoor or Bath stone"></div></div>
  <h3>South West</h3>
  <p>Bath's crescents, Dartmoor's tors, and the Cotswolds once the coaches have gone home.</p>
  <span class="count">3 guides →</span>
</a><a class="r-card" href="/coming-soon">
  <div class="thumb"><div class="img" data-ph="The North — fells and ridgelines"></div></div>
  <h3>The North</h3>
  <p>Lakeland fells, Peak District ridgelines, and a proper harbour town for fish and chips.</p>
  <span class="count">3 guides →</span>
</a><a class="r-card" href="/coming-soon">
  <div class="thumb"><div class="img" data-ph="Wales — Wye or Pembrokeshire cliffs"></div></div>
  <h3>Wales &amp; the Borders</h3>
  <p>The Wye at dawn and the far west of Pembrokeshire, castles on the way.</p>
  <span class="count">2 guides →</span>
</a><a class="r-card" href="/coming-soon">
  <div class="thumb"><div class="img" data-ph="East Anglia — big sky, wide beach"></div></div>
  <h3>East Anglia</h3>
  <p>Pine-backed beaches, shingle and salt marsh, and the best light in England.</p>
  <span class="count">2 guides →</span>
</a><a class="r-card" href="/coming-soon">
  <div class="thumb"><div class="img" data-ph="Scotland — Edinburgh rooftops"></div></div>
  <h3>Scotland</h3>
  <p>Edinburgh's closes and wynds, and the hills you can see from them.</p>
  <span class="count">1 guide →</span>
</a></div>
    <p style="margin-top:clamp(40px,6vw,56px);color:var(--sage);font-size:14.5px;line-height:1.6;max-width:56ch;">Somewhere missing? The next region gets covered when we've driven it, not before. Tell us where to go via <a href="/the-weekend-brief" style="font-weight:600;">the Brief</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- ============ FOOTER ============ -->
</Base>
